        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 6:09PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 609 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Oil City to near Ithaca to near Portland.
Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Oil City around 615 PM EDT.
Sanford and Merrill around 620 PM EDT.
Midland and Marion Springs around 625 PM EDT.
St. Charles and Freeland around 635 PM EDT.
Auburn around 640 PM EDT.
Saginaw around 645 PM EDT.
Zilwaukee around 650 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Brant, Nelson,
Carrollton, Garfield, Fenmore, Poseyville, Layton Corners, Willard,
Vernon, and Laporte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
southeastern Michigan.</instruction>
